.TH MIRROR-TOOL 1 "25 November 2020"
.SH NAME
mirror-tool \- track changes to local git mirrors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mirror-tool
.RB [ -ucq ]
.I repository
.RI [ branch ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mirror-tool
is designed to check a local
.BR git (1)
mirror
.I repository
on an optional
.I branch
for any new commits and display them using
.BR tig (1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -c
Print the number of new commits and exit.
.TP
.B -u
Update the mirror.
.TP
.B -q
Suppress the use of
.B tig
and printing of diagnostics.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GIT_DIR
Used to set the
.I repository
as the
.B git
directory.
.SH SOURCE
~/.local/bin/mirror-tool
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git (1),
.BR tig (1)
